    "body": "### Contact Details (e.g. Tox ID or email)\n\nfloppy\n\n### qTox Version\n\n1.18.2\n\n### Commit Hash\n\n_No response_\n\n### Toxcore Version\n\n_No response_\n\n### Qt Version\n\n_No response_\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Start qTox and load/create a profile\n2. enable proxy and set the address to \"user:pw@127.0.0.1\"\n3. restart\n\n### Observed Behavior\n\n- watch it fail\n- be locked out of your profile, since you cant change the proxy setting without launching\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\n1. being able to change connection related settings upfront (eg another tab in the profile selector)\n2. dont allow setting a proxy that toxcore considers invalid\n\n\n### Reproducibility\n\nAlways\n\n### Operating System\n\nOther (please specify)\n\n### Operating System version/distro/name/etc.\n\n_No response_\n\n### Relevant log output\n\n```shell\nsrc/core/toxoptions.cpp:109 : Debug: Using proxy \"user:password@xx.xx.xx.xx\" : 1080\nsrc/core/core.cpp:171 : Critical: Bad proxy, error code: 5\nsrc/persistence/profile.cpp:249 : Debug: Failed to start Toxcore\n```",
